HEADWORD: malanders
<hw>mal"an*ders</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧l"⟦ait⟧n*d⟦etil⟧rz)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>malandres</ets>, fr. L. <ets>malandria</ets>
blisters or pustules on the neck, especially in horses.]</ety>
<fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A scurfy eruption in the bend of the knee of the
fore leg of a horse. See <er>Sallenders</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>mallenders</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

